President Obama announced his intent to nominate Judge Gerard Lynch for a seat on the United States Court of Appeals for the Second Circuit and Judge Andre Davis for a seat on the United States Court of Appeals for the Fourth Circuit. Judge Lynch currently sits on the United States District Court for the Southern District of New York, while Judge Davis serves on the United States District Court for the District of Maryland. President Obama praised both judges for their records of integrity and fairness, stating that they will bring reason and even-handedness to their respective circuits. Judge Lynch, born and raised in Brooklyn, New York, has a distinguished legal career and has served in various government positions. Judge Davis, born and raised in East Baltimore, has also had a successful legal career and has been involved in teaching and judicial organizations. They are being nominated to fill vacant seats on the Second and Fourth Circuits, respectively.